{
  "text": "However, we do want to point out that the multiplicity of the two non-equivalent Weil modules found in [CITATION_1] to be constituents of I when \u2113 = 2 for the symplectic group Sp 2n (q), q odd, is indeed one. This is so because a linear character of the type described above is present in each Weil module (cf. section 4 of [CITATION_2] ).",
